SETUP________________________________________________________________________________________________
Ruby Version Manager:
  cmd:  rvm install ruby-x.x.x
  cmd:  rvm use ruby x.x.x@<appName> --create
    desc: creates a new gemset
  cmd:  gem install rails
  cmd:  rvm gemset list
  cmd:  

Creating a new API Only Application:
  cmd: rails new api -T --api -d postgresql

  Add gems (Development Sections Only)
  gem 'rspec-rails', '~>4.0.1'
  gem 'factory_bot_rails'

  cmd: rails generate rspec:install

  Substitute the RSpec.configure section of the /spec/rails_helper.rb file as follows:
    RSpec.configure do |config|
      # Remove this line if you're not using ActiveRecord or ActiveRecord fixtures
      # config.fixture_path = "#{::Rails.root}/spec/fixtures"
      config.include FactoryBot::Syntax::Methods

  OTHER GEMS (added throughout course):
  To format all JSON responses throughout the app:
    1) add gem to gem file: gem 'jsonapi-serializer' 
    2) cmd: rails g serializer <model> <atrributes>
      ie: rails g serializer article title content slug
    3) Add a serializer method to your model's controller:
      ie:   def serializer
              ArticleSerializer
            end
    4) Add Serializer to your return data.
      ie:   def index
              # render json: Article.all, status: :ok       #BEFORE SERIALIZER
              articles = Article.all
              render json: serializer.new(articles), status: :ok  #AFTER
            end
  

BACKEND_______________________________________________________________________________
Note: All of the following should be performed in the backend/api folder

Generate a model (notice that the model is in singular form)
  cmd:  rails g model <column_dame>:<type_declaration>
    ie:   rails g model article title content:text slug 
  cmd:  rails db:migrate

Generate a controller:
  cmd:  rails g controller <colum_name>


RAILS CONSOLE_______________________________________________________________________
  cmd: rails c

Create new item
  cmd: Article.create(title: 'Sample article', content: 'My awesome article', slug: 'sample-article')


RSPEC__________________________
To run rspec:
  cmd:  rspec
  cmd:  rspec --format=documentation
Expectation Syntax for your rspec methods:
  expect (value) to (matcher)


MISC. GEM NOTES:
Action => Pagination:
  Gem 'jsom-pagination'



ROUTING_____________________________
To Get all routes:
  cmd:  rails routes
To get a filtered list of routes
  cmd:  rails routes -g <route_name>        
  cmd:  rails routes | grep <route_name>
To filter out routes that are auto generated by rails
  cmd:  rails routes | grep -v rails

To create new routes in the routes.rb file
    get '/articles', to: 'articles#index'
    resources :articles
    resources :articles, only: [:index]        